        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Request.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Request.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Request.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Response.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Response.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Response.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/Headers.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Headers.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/fetch/Headers.cpp\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"mozilla-firefox/firefox\",\n      \"path\": \"dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Cross-org WebIDL to DOM Binding Discovery - Fetch API Analysis\\n\\nThis analysis identifies the WebIDL interface definitions for the Fetch API in Firefox and their corresponding C++ binding implementations.\\n\\nFetch API Interface Mappings:\\n\\n1. Request Interface:\\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Request.webidl\\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Request.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Request.cpp\\n   - Description: Defines the Request interface for the Fetch API (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#request-class). The C++ implementation provides the Request constructor and methods for controlling request parameters including method, URL, headers, credentials, cache policy, and abort signal handling.\\n\\n2. Response Interface:\\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Response.webidl\\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Response.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Response.cpp\\n   - Description: Defines the Response interface for the Fetch API (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#response-class). Includes response status, headers, body handling, and static factory methods for creating error and redirect responses.\\n\\n3. Headers Interface:\\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/Headers.webidl\\n   - C++ Header: dom/fetch/Headers.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Headers.cpp\\n   - Description: Defines the Headers interface for managing HTTP header collections (http://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#headers-class). Provides methods for appending, deleting, getting, setting headers, and iteration support.\\n\\n4. FetchEvent Interface:\\n   - WebIDL Definition: dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl\\n   - C++ Header: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h\\n   - C++ Implementation: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp\\n   - Description: Defines the FetchEvent interface for Service Worker fetch event handling (http://slightlyoff.github.io/ServiceWorker/spec/service_worker/index.html). The FetchEvent class extends ExtendableEvent and provides access to the intercepted request, preload response promise, client IDs, and the respondWith() method for providing custom responses.\\n\\nAdditional Context:\\n- The dom/webidl/Fetch.webidl file defines the Body mixin and other core Fetch API types (BodyInit, FetchReadableStreamReadData) that are used across Request and Response interfaces.\\n- All WebIDL files are located in the mozilla-firefox/firefox repository under dom/webidl/.\\n- Request, Response, and Headers implementations are in dom/fetch/ directory.\\n- FetchEvent implementation is in dom/serviceworkers/ directory because it is Service Worker specific.\\n- The implementations use WebIDL bindings generated from these IDL files, providing JavaScript-accessible DOM APIs.\"\n}\n",
            "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json"
          },
